02/02/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested a man Tuesday (February 1st) suspected of crimes against humanity committed in Sarajevo in 1992. Sasa Baricanin, 42, was detained in Pale. He is suspected of taking part in the murder, rape, looting and intimidation of Bosniak civilians, along with Veselin Vlahovic, known as the "Monster of Grbavica". He was extradited from Spain to BiH last year. (RTRS, Srna, Tanjug, AP - 01/02/11)
